UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1442
1 keeping me in close contact with my Eastern Kentucky constituents and providing me
2 with vital insights on her region of the state [...] I am incredibly grateful for her public
3 service and am proud to have her on my team," said Senator McConnell; and
4 WHEREAS, the late Chamber of Commerce Director Randy Smith wrote, "Donna
5 is naturally gifted with a terrific personality and one that offers her the ability to
6 communicate with anyone she meets . . . She is career-oriented and self-motivated and
7 not intimidated to set lofty goals that she will work diligently to reach."; and
8 WHEREAS, Donna Sue Baker is a mother of three children, Jonathan and his wife
9 Jordan, Donavon, and Martina Faith McClure;
10 NOW, THEREFORE,
11 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
12 Kentucky:
13 Section 1. The Senate hereby honors Donna Sue Baker for her service to her
14 community and the Commonwealth as a dedicated servant.
15 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor of Donna Sue
16 Baker.
17 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
18 Resolution to Senator Brandon Storm.
